#### Line-side monitoring equipment

In the ceaseless quest for operational safety and efficiency, the [Midland Main Line](/Midland_Main_Line) is equipped with a variety of sophisticated line-side train monitoring equipment. These silent sentinels are designed to detect potential issues with rolling stock before they escalate into something altogether more problematic. Among the most crucial are [hot axle box detectors (HABD)](/Hot_box_(railway)) and [wheel impact load detectors (WILD)](/Wheel_impact_load_detector), often referred to by the rather charming moniker 'Wheelchex'. These devices represent the vigilant, unseen eyes of the railway, constantly scanning for anomalies.

